{
  "texts": [
    "In general, federated models outperform the local counterparts, both in terms of RMSE and r. The benefit of FL over the LL setting is particularly evident for the TSK-FRBS and especially in the non-i.i.d.",
    "settings.Federated TSK-FRBS and federated MLP-NN achieve comparable performances.",
    "The most noticeable difference occurs in the NIID-F setting, in which the two metrics provide diverse insights: on one hand, RMSE indicates that the deviation of predictions from true values is lower for the MLP-NN (10.268) compared to the TSK-FRBS (16.848); on the other hand, predictions and true values are more correlated for TSK-FRBS (r = 0.461) than for MLP-NN (r = 0.205).The non-i.i.d.",
    "setting with quantity skew (NIID-Q) does not harm particularly the performance of the models: RMSE and r values are comparable to those of the IID setting, for both TSK-FRBS and MLP-NN.",
    "In the case of TSK-FRBS, the simple average of the performances measured on the training sets shows poor performance for the LL setting, where some models likely suffer from low data availability."
  ]
}